snippet.textDisplay:
Hello Coke Studio India team,

I'm writing to share my disappointment with your music productions. As a fan of Coke Studio Pakistan and Coke Studio Bangla, I've come to expect a certain level of quality and excellence in your music. Unfortunately, your releases haven't quite lived up to those standards.

I miss the soulful melodies, the fusion of genres, and the raw talent that CS Pakistan and CS Bangla consistently deliver. I hope you'll take my feedback constructively and strive to bring back the magic that made Coke Studio a household name.

Looking forward to seeing improvement in your future productions!

Best regards,
Shakir (A Coke Studio Fan)
snippet.textOriginal:
Hello Coke Studio India team,

I'm writing to share my disappointment with your music productions. As a fan of Coke Studio Pakistan and Coke Studio Bangla, I've come to expect a certain level of quality and excellence in your music. Unfortunately, your releases haven't quite lived up to those standards.

I miss the soulful melodies, the fusion of genres, and the raw talent that CS Pakistan and CS Bangla consistently deliver. I hope you'll take my feedback constructively and strive to bring back the magic that made Coke Studio a household name.

Looking forward to seeing improvement in your future productions!

Best regards,
Shakir (A Coke Studio Fan)

I don't know anyone noticed it or not but I did. This song definitely is lit fire from Coke Studio India. 
But I find a lot of similarities of this song's visuals with the visuals of 2 songs from Coke Studio Pakistan. 
One song is Phir Milenge from Season 14 and second one is Aayi Aayi from Season 15.

BTW, India is elevating it's COKE STUDIO platform. Glad to see that.
Being Indian, I love Coke Studio Pakistan much more because of the level of authenticity and musicality they serve in the platter💜

Jai Hind😇
